caption: Love the food here, absolutely amazing. Their Jinya bun is a must have!
The food is amazing! The staff is awesome!
Went for lunch. Food was excellent, I got 5 out of 10 stars for spiciness on the ramen dish and it was just perfect. Great flavor. Service was good.

My boyfriend and I had a late night and everywhere was closed nearby just about so we came here close to closing time and the staff greeted us and took care of us regardless. Everyone was very nice, laid-back, and helpful with the menu since it was our first time. The atmosphere was cool and the food was delicious! He got the Wonton Chicken Ramen and I got the Sprouting Up Ramen. We also ordered the Takoyaki-Octopus Balls as the waiter recommended which were where very interesting. The texture was a little strange for me personally but it was good! My ramen was amazing! The brussel sprouts were perfectly cooked and the broth was delicious! Would definitely recommend if you like ramen!
Ramen was great and broth was full of flavor. Even the wife liked it and she's not much into trying new things.

I am by no means a ramen expert, but in my somewhat picky, non-expert opinion, this is really good ramen.  Ramen is actually one of my favorite foods to try in most every city I visit. I'm usually disappointed, but not at Jinya. It's actually flavorful, and the broth isn't watery.  One thing to note: the last time I went they had a spicy scale of 1-10 to select from. It turns out 2 is like medium hot salsa, 3 is like hot salsa, and everything beyond that is straight fire. I asked for 6 and was gently (and thankfully) recalibrated.
This was our First time at Jinya and it  was great. The restaurant was very clean, super friendly staff, excellent service, delicious food and good prices. Can’t wsit to go back!!!
Great food. Great service, we will be returning.
Always seems to be some kind of issue at this location. I'd recommend the sandy springs location for the best experience.

Walked in over an hour before ‘Google’ said they we’re closed and we’re turned away due to ‘being closed’. Either google gets it right or nothing. Worst services ever. Google and Jinya include. Less than 1 star
Their staff are the rudest I’ve ever experienced, furthermore trying to tell a customer they don’t sell something that is clearly on their menu is bloody stupid!
Tonkotsu red ramen was excellent.

I just ordered through Uber Eats and my order arrived completely unsecured. I immediately called the restaurant to express my concern it being Covid and all. The manager told me they send all the orders out this way because people complain about sealed bags.😐 What he didn’t know is I am also a food service manager, and it is completely unacceptable to send orders out unsecured even before covid. Restaurants should not staple packages, but it is common practice to use tape or logo stickers. I’ve even recently seen bags that come with an adhesive strip. Unfortunately I can’t order Jinya via Uber Eats again. 🤷🏾‍♂️
Best ever!

I've only gotten takeout from here but it's great. I'm a long time patron at the Sandy springs location, and I'm happy there's one in alpharetta now! My favorite is the pork buns and the tonkatsu black.
Great food! Very flavorful and has something for everyone. I loved the ramen and the mochi dessert. They are really good and timely at Togo’s as well!
I ordered spicy chicken, the soup is really tasty.
Best vegan Ramen I've ever had... better than places in New York City.
Very good. Except i order something they do not have it at  the mean time.
Unacceptable wait times, and they make you wait outside in the rain.

Authentic ramen taste experience with a variety of taste profiles. Ambience is modern with asian elements woven in. Staff was diligent about practicing safety standards. Patrons were seated at the required distancing rules, and so it didn't feel crowded. The noise levels and music were not overbearing, just right.  The food was brilliant. The bar is well stocked, but seriously go for the chilled sake. That's what you're here for anyway. If available, the bar seat offers best experience as the bartenders are amazing. Ask for Zak or Pak. They'll regale you with their stories and anecdotes.
Bought chicken ramen and got an over cooked egg and not so tasty ramen. I have been to other location at Sandy springs and that was much better.
I would eat there literally every day (if my wife didn't murder me for it, lol). Best ramen in town by a mile.
If you like ramen, then you'll like Jinya
Amazing Ramen!
Def. recommend Spicy chicken soup! So good!
Love this place. Prompt, friendly service, and the tonkatsu red is da bomb! I'll be coming back for sure.
Always great noodles with speedy service! Never disappoints!!! 😊

First time ever going to Ramen place, couldn't be happier with the meal. Menu is great and not overwhelming. Everything my group had was really well made. Staff is very knowledgeable and friendly. Can't say a single bad thing about this place

Was hoping that it lived up to their reviews, however it was a huge disappointment. Staff was very inattentive, took nearly 40 minutes to even place my order, and I literally had to call a server over. The food was mediocre, and we had to ask for utensils, and our appetizers came out at the end of our meal. When it did finally show up, they spilled the sauce all over my dang food. Get it together.

We came in on a full saturday night without reservations and the hostess had us sat in 20 min with no hassle. The quality of ingredients used here is outstanding. The pork used in my tonkotsu soup particularly was absolutely melt in your mouth tender and the broth was robust with umami flavors. The noodle itself was cooked perfectly with some bite to it, and had a nice hearty consistency perfectly complimenting every flavor in the soup. On the side we had octopus balls which were interesting in texture; it may not appeal to a lot but the sauce plated with the balls were explosions of flavor that were amazing. Come here for some GOOD AUTHENTIC ramen.
My family can't get enough of this place.  Love every bit of it.  The bao (Jinya Buns) and to die for.

This Jinya is great when you eat in but when you take out it's not too good. I came here at night last week and they forgot most of the ingredients in the vegan ramen. Like it was just the soup, ramen, and green onions. No sesame seeds, garlic crisps.  The staff is super friendly and professional and they wore masks. I would definitely come back to dine in again.

Normally we go to Jinya in Buckhead, but we tried this location. It's the same great customer service and food. This location has dining inside and outside. In my opinion, this location is bigger in size than the Sandy Springs location but a little bigger than the Buckhead location. Parking at this location could be problematic cause the location is in the town square and street parking near it is limited. Bright side - there is handicap parking across the way from the restaurant. After eating, you can walk around to the shops in the square or sit in the park area across the street.
Very good ramen. Wide selection of Sake. Takoyaki was some of the best we've had so far. Staggered tables for social distancing and they clean the tables very well.
Great tasting ramen. So far my favorite ramen outside japan. If your in the area definitely worth stopping by. I recommend the takoyaki for a appatizer it's really good.
Friendly service, nice food and a nice vibe overall.
JINYA is a reliable place to go to whenever you want ramen, this location has great service and food without a steep price!
Horrible service. Menu is incorrect. They’re out of the ingredients they say are in the menu. Basically it’s like ordering a cheeseburger and it comes with no cheese.

Worst experience I've had with a hostess. She did everything in her power to not give us a table, despite being many of them open and the fact that we added our names to the waitlist ahead of time. She initially said that there's no outdoor seating at all, despite the fact that we visually saw that there were people seated outside. Then, she said she couldn't add any tables because the waitresses were too busy. But then, even when one of the outdoor tables finished, she said there still would be another 30 minute wait. This wasted a lot of our afternoon.

Best ramen! Wanted to try the chicken wonton, but they were out of it (must be that good, so next time!) but spicy chicken was delicious. Service was great, food came out fast and hot and the bartender was super friendly and patient with our sake questions. Will be back!

A wonderful location and ambiance, excellent service, and a delicious menu. We tried three different ramen dishes - JINYA Chicken Ramen, Spicy Chicken Ramen, Premium Tonkotsu Red, and, the Kids Meal. Additional toppings are available to further enrich the experience, albeit not indispensable - everything was delightful!  Perfect for a dinner out with friends, family, or a casual date. 🥟🍜🥃
We love a hot bowl of slurry cilantro or vegetable bowl on a cold day. We sit at the bar and the service is always outstanding. So glad they opened one in Atlanta.
First time there and the food was great and service was awesome. Will be back
Flying Vegan Harvest is always delightful!
Staff up front wasn’t Pleasant. See something more was going on wasn’t happy.

We had a hankering for some good ramen to hit the spot after a long road trip.  With good reviews, we decided to JINYA a try.  We were seated quickly.  Service was friendly and helpful.  We tried several appetizers, ramen dishes and topped everything off with some warm sake for the chilly evening.  I'll be back.
Oh yeah!!

Need to be a little bit more diverse minded towards black African-American customers… Front Greeter LIED about seating claiming no availability initially.  When we were seated…Customer service was not that great… Did not check on us during the course of our meal and had to ask for water refills… Unacceptable service!!!
Best ramen in town!

Very tasty and fresh food. The service was fast and very pleasant. The restaurant was clean and had inviting atmosphere.  I had the chicken wonton ramen and it was exactly what I needed. Soothing, warm and light food.
Great vibe, great ramen
My favorite Ramen. Great service and amazing food. My favorite is the chicken wanton ramen!!! Best food ever on a cold night!
Wifes favorite place to eat.   They are seating guest at every other table.
Ramens were cooked to perfection. My young kids loved the place from starters to entrees.
Service is superb. Prices fair and the Ramen is deadly addictive. Gyoza potstickers are a great way to start as a single diner or for a couple.

Love this place!
Excelente food!

Great food, prices and service!

Quite a lot of seating and the food is absolutely delicious. As a vegetarian there are so many options and choices to pick from which keeps things fresh and wanting to come back for more! I'm excited to go back and devour more!
Best Ramen in Atlanta
Excellent ramen. Flavorful, fresh. Excellent atmosphere and service as well. No complaints here.
The are a great addition to downtown Alpharetta. They have the best pot stickers, and they offer vegan meals. All very tasty.
Worst Ramen restaurant in Alpharetta.
Amazing. Best ramen, period.

The food was very flavorful with every bite. I love how they prepare their Brussel sprouts. The fried chicken was crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside. I tried the thin and thick noodles and I preferred the thick ones personally. I would love to come back.
I love the vegan bowl there
Top 5 Favorite ramen restaurants. Great options. The wonton chicken ramen with chili oil is my personal favorite!
This place clearly knows how to take care of their clients. Consistently with a friendly approach. The food is reasonably priced, always delicious and neat.
Great tasting Ramen.
Totsumai red is the best
Delicious... my first time but several friends favorite place so I had to try. I had the Shrimp Wonton and my son had the Spicy Chicken Ramenbut we both stayed with the Pork Belly Bun.

Amazing place to get Ramen. Customer service is amazing and the food is to die for! I recommend this spot to anyone that loves Ramen and nice time. Definitely coming back for my birthday on the 7th of December!
Thick soup tasted great and little bit greasy. Overall nice place to dine in or take out.
The best ramen - the eggs are amazing!
Great food and good price. Worth the wait.
Great food and great service. 10/10. Perfect spot for a date.
Best ramen restaurant in the area. California poke bowl is 10/10.
Delicious food and great service!
Delicious!
friendly staff.  great food. great service

My boyfriend and I went in for a late lunch today and we always enjoy Jinya but today stood out for me. The host was very friendly and quick to greet us. We sat on the patio and Daniel took wonderful care of us. He made sure to let us know about the ongoing happy hour and warned me when I ordered a level 10 spicy ramen. I still went for it and boy is it hot, but absolutely delicious. Food came out super quick. We both thoroughly enjoyed our food as well as the awesome service. Thank you, Daniel!
Great atmosphere.
Great
Absolutely amazing food and service. 10/10.
Service and food was fantastic!
(Translated by Google) Excellent attention, the place is cool, the food well presented and delicious  (Original) Excelente atencion, el local esta cool,  la comida bien presentada y deliciosa
Best Ramen anywhere. Trt their new shrimp wonton. It's the bomb.
Great location, great environment, and great food. This is the best location of them all in Georgia.
Great!

Visited a little while back, and I'm about to head that way today! I always love the delicious broth with the spicy chicken ramen. The staff is extremely friendly, and the food amazing. I highly recommend checking Jinya Ramen out!
Their ramen is amazing....it is a great place

I go to Jinya with my boyfriend very frequently! We love this location and the service :-) I don't know the name of one girl that works there, but she is amazing. She wears Doc Martens and has colored hair. The first time she served us, she was super sweet and really attentive. We recently went a few days ago, and although she wasn't our server at first, she stopped by and remembered that we like to order hot sauce with our Takoyaki and asked us if we needed some! I really appreciate her & will always go back~
i love their Vegan/vegetarian options

Great staff and beautifully decorated Interior. Service was efficent and customers were handled properly. Food shows a lot of care and effort. Tastes good too.
Excellent food with friendly staff
Always a great experience and the food is to die for 🍜🥰😋

My favorite ramen (and staff) of any ramen bar I've been to. Great atmosphere, even if you're outside on the patio looking at the hidden(ish) little garden. Also a favorite for takeout and reheats well so order extra if getting takeout. I suggest adding the spicy bamboo shoots (no little rectangles here).  You'll be here a bit since it's all made to order... But totally worth it
Really good quality ramen
Best Ramen Bar in the city!
Jinya is my favorite Ramen spot. The broth is always delicious and the ingredients fresh. I love the Sproutin Up Ramen. It is fantastic.
Loved it!! Great flavors and delicious!
Ramen is off the chain. Service was okay at best. Been sitting here wait for sweet tea for no joke 20 minutes.
I usually go to the one in Buckhead, but it is closed for dine in. This location hit the spot. Great service, even better food. Also try the octopus balls!!!🐙

Excellent and authentic Ramen. It was my first time here and everything was great. The bartender was very friendly and attentive, and happily answered all my questions about the menu. Be careful with the spiciness level. If you can't eat spicy food, don't request a spice level more than a 0 or 1. I'll definitely be back soon.
I always come for the fried chicken and jinya bun 😌 so good
Always so delicious! Some of the best ramen in Atlanta
Wonderful place to eat!!!
I love the food here. The service is lovely and the workers are nice. The ramen that I get is always packed with flavor and it warms you from the inside out. I highly recommend this restaurant.
Great ambiance.

Social distancing champs! You go in and they have everyone properly distanced not like a lot of places where they say they're taking precautions and just cram everyone in. The actual food was delicious.  The spicy chicken ramen was great and just the right amount of spicy for me. You can always ask for chile paste to make it hotter or order the Hot version but this was good enough that it was hot enough and built in spice but didn't overpower my whole experience. The creamy spicy shrimps where the winners for me!
Nice one.
Excellent! Takoyaki and Black Ramen were delicious...!!! I strongly recommend it.
Thoroughly enjoyed the Jinya Tonkotsu Black Ramen. Extremely flavorful broth. The noodles 🍜  had a nice chew and clung to the broth well. Definitely worth checking out if your in downtown Alpharetta.

Ramen is as good as usual, and the good thing is the premium red tonkatsu ramen is back, and I'm warning you, level 5 is really really really spicy. I am a big fan of Jinya ramen Sandy Springs, and I'm glad that they have a new restaurant here in the Alpharetta finally. The Alpharetta one is more spacious and also comes with a beautiful patio. They keep the social distance for both outside and inside sitting, so it is an excellent place to some get dine-in experience during the pandemic times.
So yummy! Very clean and always good service. Everything I've tried there has been delicious. The kids meal is amazing too. My little ones love it!
Wowowow. Incredible selection, vegan options, fresh veggies. My two picky children flippin loved the kid's meal.
Excellent! Better ramen than those in Japan.

If it wasn't for the horrible wait time. , this place would definitely be a 5-star for me. I know that once the weather warms up, they'll be able to use their outdoor space. But right now it's just really inconvenient for a late date night ramen run. I first went to Jinya in atlanta and I was sold! The food and the service are just great. I cant say how authentic things are but I'm very happy. I always get the spicy chicken ramen, add mushrooms and bok choy.

I was doing an Uber Eats delivery and the bag ripped so I went back inside to ask for another paper bag or for them to staple it back. I wouldn’t want the customer to think their food was tampered with. The snobby woman at the front door refused to staple the bag back shut and gave me a regular paper bag. Not the same kind the food was in which was nicer. The bag with the food in it still had a huge rip in the front. Bad internal customer service.

First time there & had a great time. Food is awesome & I love the leechie martini. Don't know if I spelled it right but it was deliciously refreshing. Wish this place was closer to where I live cause I would eat there every week. Very friendly service too.

I never write reviews but this place is so amazing I just had to. The service was great and their vegan ramen was AMAZING! Usually vegan ramen doesn’t have a lot of flavor but their broth was so rich. I loved it! If you’re vegan I definitely recommend trying their ramen. Absolutely delicious.
Excellent service and the food was awesome!
Sprouting up ramen

Ordered online per recommendation from colleagues and I'd agree that this place is awesome. The taste is great, I ordered a pickup during COVID-19 hence can't comment much on the place but there seemed to be decent room inside. I like asian spicy food and hence ordered the Spicy Chicken Ramen (hot). Per my standards the HOT was American hot not Asian but the taste is awesome. Also ordered Flying Vegan Harvest and Spicy Creamy Vegan which were OK. I'd definitely recommend this place if you like Ramen.
Yummy ramen for a rainy(or not rainy) day.  Fast and friendly service,  great location.
Our Ramen fix - this is the go to place. Definitely recommend it!
The best ramen in town, nothing more to add. Tonkotsu Black and Spicy Umami just rock. R'amen
Loved the opening and food!
Have only experienced their food via take-out, and everything I ordered was fantastic. Definitely a must try in Alpharetta.
Delicious

Really great place to get Ramen. The broth is fresh, and so are the ingredients and at a fair price to boot. Sure, it's Americanized ramen, but you can't deny that it's well made. The workers are friendly and try their hardest to keep the place clean. Only criticism I have is some of the ramen served uses too much salt, but this usually isn't an issue. Totally recommend it!
The food is always delicious and the atmosphere is so inviting. I highly recommend the spicy chicken ramen. My waitress, Jo, is always on top of it and very friendly.
This was amazing! Great food. Great staff. The restaurant atmosphere was lovely. I liked how its a bit hidden. Can't wait to return!
I always stop by buying some food in here. I liked the prompt service and well prepared dishes. Kudos.
Definitely we will be back.
Awesome food
Excellent Noodle and Cha-shu Don!
De. Li. Cious. Little pricey but worth it. Go healthy or not with good food and drink
The best vegetarian ramen ive had in my life. The creamy broth is on a different level.
best ramen in town!
This has become my favorite for the premium red tonkotso.
Good ramen place.  Sumptuous spicy ramen.  A little off the main entrance so not so easy to find.   Servers were helpful.   Messed up my order a little.
Great food - very flavorful and a great atmosphere 👍
Staff is amazing and food

Delicious, I loved it. When they say something is spicy, it actually is spicy. 5 of 10 was the perfect about of spicy, and I love spicy as it can be. My friends warned me to not go any higher and I was happy with the result.
Delicious. Totally. Very nice place. Good attention. But expensive
Fantastic ramen. The brussel sprouts are bomb. Be prepared to wait.
Served hot and taste phenomenal. A great place to grab a bite in this cold weather.
Great food and very friendly staff! Don't forget to try the Jinya bun, it's awesome.
Clean, organized kitchen. Food was amazing! Did take out this time, but looking forward to dining in next time.
Good food, good vibe. Best place to eat ramen.

This was my first time at this trendy ramen bar! And I must say the staff were excellent. Especially the Bartender/Hostess Jasmine who greeted me with a smile and warm personality, definitely going back for seconds and you should too!😉👌🏽
Reliable ramen spot with a nice range of options, even if you just like noodles and chicken :)
The vegan options at this place are everything.... wow, I just really enjoyed the food here and ate so much of it. Would highly recommend this to anyone.

This place has such a cozy feel to it. It was packed on a Friday night. Lots of families eat here and there is a great seat anywhere in the house in view of a tv.  Food was fresh and drinks were amazing.  Tried the chicken curry bowl. Love the bowls they serve food with. It gives it a really nice cultural feel.  All staff were friendly and said goodbye.  I am coming back to try the ramen.
There curry is pretty good would buy again
Awesome food, the spicy creamy vegan ramen is my favorite thing on the menu hands down.
Service and food was excellent. A very laid back experience. Tasty Ramen!
Lots of options for the veggie friendly crew, spicy edamame is SPICY! but delicious and the tempura brussel sprouts are crispy but tender! Wash it down with a japanese Hitachino Nest beer!
Best Vegan Ramen I've ever had
Good noodle
Great food
By far the best Ramen in GA!!!
Great !

Surprisingly disappointed as this restaurant is located at a very high traffic location. Red ramen was too salty and thick, noodle was overcooked and soup was not warm enough. Probably worst ramen place I've tried.
Really flavorful ramen. Love that you can order more noodles
Great food and atmosphere
I really like their dishes. I always get great customer service there. The place is clean and the workers are always super friendly. Will come visit again.
Fantastic

We came here for our anniversary lunch and  loved the food. We tried Spicy chicken ramen and Jinya Ramen .. both were amazing.. Food was delicious and portion size was just right.. they have this huge bar area to sit and eat just like places in Japan. must try restaurant for comfort Japanese food was  !!
Excellent ramen with fresh quality ingredients. Slightly pricey but worth the price!!
Got the spicy chicken ramen and it was pretty great. Wasn't super spicy so I had to add some more hot sauce to it. Definitely recommend if you like noodles and broth. Love a nice noodle.
Great new location, nice decor, friendly staff and fast service makes this go for food just that more amazing. Had the Tonkatzu Ramen with crispy chicken and let me just rave about the egg 😛
Wonderful place and delicious food. I had the spicy chicken ramen with crispy chicken and salad. Highly recommended
Great food amazing vegan options!

We have eaten at Jinya five or six times. The noodle dishes are great. I was not a fan of the rice bowls. The rice bowls were very bland snd not as well prepared as the noodles. I would recommend staying with what they do best.
Lot of variety. First course are very good. Quick service, generous size of dishes.
buns. need i say more
Get in early or late. This place is amazing but it's super busy almost always. Really great ramen.
Yum! Expensive but they'll refill your noodles.
Excellent ramen. My only disappointment was our food was served 10 mins apart.
Love the kale noodles!  Wait staff was knowledgeable and efficient. Food was excellent. Highly recommend!
First time coming here, excellent service ! The ramen was really  delicious , I can’t wait to stop by and get more !
Excellent food. Was not a ramen fan until eating at Jinya.
Great food, great atmosphere!
The food and service were very good. The restaurant was quite loud so be prepared for that.
One of my favorite spots. Great food and service
Fantastic ramen, best ramen place I have been to on the east coast. Spicy chicken ramen was amazing!
Excellent ramen, wonderful variety.  Reasonable prices

Excellent!  I believe this location is a little more authentic and mindful of food preparation than the Sandy Springs location.  You'll never get the exact same as if you were in Japan but I'm impressed with the food here.  Very tasty.

The food was great. I had the flying vegan harvest which had a good kick of spice to it, but not at all too much if you're not really into that. They have three fully vegetarian(vegan) options, and I'm so down to try the other two!
Plenty of Options to choose from!!! Great taste! Mini Vegan Tacos are so cute and yummy!!!!

Really good, fresh ramen in large portions. Friendly, efficient staff. I had the shrimp wonton which was rich and flavorful. I could get addicted to the stuff, lol. The place is small and fills up quickly for lunch. There's limited street parking, but a free parking deck a block away. Great addition to the restaurants in Alpharetta city center.
The food was really good. I enjoyed it a lot. My ramen broth was really rich and the seasoned egg was my favorite part of it. The staff was friendly.

If you love ramen and have not come by here yet, do make the time to come here. I cannot eat ramen at any other restaurants after I've been introduced to Jinya. I highly recommend their spicy shrimp tempura as well as their Jinya bun. It will literally melt in your mouth. I sometimes crave just the bun. Don't get me started with the ramen. The portions are more than enough. Service is excellent. I usually don't like waiting to eat, but at Jinya Ramen Bar, I don't mind waiting at all.
Best. Ramen. Ever. Service also outstanding. I want to live next door.
Not a good option for gluten free.  Edamame, cauliflower, plain rice or seaweed salad are your only options.  The cauliflower small plate was good but I'm still hungry

I really like the place since I moved to Atlanta. We used to go to the one near Sandy Springs for lunch and was pretty impressed with their food. This one is specific to the kne in Alpharetta and we visited the day next to new year in the evening and it was busy as expected. I was taking my friends who were visiting from SFO. They were new to this type of food and were ready to try it. We had both vegeterian and meat eaters in the group. To my surprise this place was catering to both the types with a great menu. Special mention to the person who served us and she was great and helped the veggies with her recommendations and was able to customize it to their needs. Overall I would say this place is a must visit in Atlanta. 5 star for all categories

Love it. This places has a great selection of Ramen. Features regular seating, high chair seating and outdoors. Great food(has veg options too), quick service and interesting interior decor. Highly recommended
Great food, fast service
We sat at the bar last night. Service and food was excellent.
It was delicious, I'm here now eating it again!

First time ever eating at Jinya. There was about a 30 minute wait but didn't take much to kill the time. This was my first real ramen experience and I must say I was impressed. Nothing like I expected to be honest. I think I had the Sprouting Up Ramen with pork. Super flavorful. Not heavy so I didn't feel guilty and every filling. Definitely going to go back to try other ramen dishes and other items on the menu.
Great food

Loved the ambience. The vibe is awesome. Best part is they have vegan and vegetarian options available. The spicy creamy vegetable ramen was top notch. The broth was delicious. Definitely a must visit place.
Ramen is amazing 😍🙌
Some truly great ramen. Amazing broths and very nice appetizers. Definitely order the takoyaki. Very recommended.
Nice place and location, good food
Had a long wait as it is very popular right now so consider getting name in and then shopping. But ramen was great and felt prices were a good value. Definitely recommend
So glad I dont have to travel far for my favorite ramen
Killer ramen... worth the wait if there is one.  Chef's special is truly special.  Slurp slurp!
This place is in need of a (new) management. Food is ok, but service is terribly slow and the wait is unbearable.

Went here for lunch a month ago when there were barely people here, and paid $38 for 2 of the same ramen dishes.  Only had about 5-6oz of broth in each bowl at the most. The noodles were half uncooked as I could taste the uncooked bits. The veggie ramen I ordered came with 3 spinach leaves flakes and maybe half an inch of cut scallion...it was supposed to have a lot of toppings per the pics and menu description.  I can see the ready made noodles dropped in the water to be cooked. Not sure how much lazier and sloppier a ramen place can get when it's charging on the top end of ramen pricing, yet doesn't cook its own noodles and serves undercooked noodles, virtually no broth, and no toppings.  Truly, the worst ramen I ever consumed in my life. Major rip off. Like most businesses, lots of fake reviews on here, too.
This is the best new restaurant to hit Alpharetta.  Absolutely delicious, great service, fair pricing, tons of food and fun atmosphere.

First time at the Sandy Springs location was very positive a few years ago and had similar expectations for this location. Ordered the Tonkotsu Black and suspect the bowl I got was towards the bottom of the pot. It had the consistency of thick stew and was overly chunky and salty. We ordered one croquette as well but it was still partially frozen. We got it replaced but the charge remained on our tab.  I appreciate the affirmation of my personal belief that trendy atmospheres in high traffic locations tend to deliver sub-par food experiences. Keep expectations in check if you're expecting anything similar to Japan/CA/NYC!
this place was amazing! everything about it was great, customer service, food, atmosphere, etc. it is a great dinner place with a bar too. love it here
Very good food, but service was a little slow. Huge portion....enough for leftovers.
Great atmosphere and good food.

Below average service. Out of every drink ordered they were out of. Waitress could not tell what they did or didn't have. Waitress did not know WiFi password. Average food. It was good, but definitely not worth the $50 for two dishes, a coke, and one green tea. Below average atmosphere. The 'ambient' music was so loud the customers had to talk loudly over it. In turn they had to speak over each other. There were only a few tables taken when my group was there. The employees had to announce a new patron by calling it out and every employee had to respond. Could not hear people beside me at the table unless we spoke loudly over the constant noise. It made the experience frustrating at best.  Overall the service was poor, the food was moderate, and overpriced.
I don’t know who is our server and multiple people come ask if we ordered or not. It takes long time to get our foods. They give our order to next table.
Came during a lunch rush but was seated fairly quickly. Waited a little while for the food, but it's worth it. Very friendly staff.
Use Yelp app to wait-list beforehand, you will thank me later.
The food was okay. Ramen was respectable, but the other food was so so. One thing that bugged me was the soft drinks in a cans rather than free refills.
Best Jinya I've been to, they actually have a good amount of flavor in the broth.
Went there for the 1st time real cute place tucked in the side just happened to stumble on it. Really good food and great service
Love this spot, whether date night or lunch hour great food at a great price....
Outstanding
Great food!! Will definitely be returning! Can't give it 5 cuz ive only tried on bowl so far!

Fresh food! Great friendly service. Had the spicy chicken ramen and gyoza. Noodles were flavorful and the chicken perfectly tender. Highly recommended. There is a free parking deck just around the corner.
Yup. They nailed it. Awesome Ramen. Beautiful build-out. So nice to have them in North Fulton.
New location closer to home, same tasty Noddles, great service, my new go-to place for Ramen Noddles,
First time there, I really enjoyed the vegetable ramen soup. Add a little of spicy sauce and seasoning ginger sauce if you want a kick. Will definitely go back for more.
Great experience and awesome food!!!!
BEST Poke/Sushi Bowl ever. The small is enough for one person. It's recently opened, so it was packed for lunch, but we only waited about 10 minutes.
Jinya ramens are the best in town. Fried chicken appetizer was very good. Bigger space than other locations and great service.
This is a great venue to get authentic ramen that can be spiced to suit your pallette!

BEWARE: People with Shellfish Allergies 1. I was disappointed to find out that they make their pork and chicken broth with seasoning that has shellfish added to it.  Since I am allergic to shellfish, I could not have any of the meat based Ramen.  They said that their vegetable based broth but I prefer the meat based broth. 2. The service was also disappointing .They delivered my did late claiming that they had a shortage of staff. My dish was probably the simplest to prepare. Tokyo Curry Rice and Spicy Tuna mini tacos...
Delicious! My lunch crew all loved the food here. I'm keto so I'd love to see an option for zucchini noodles.

Good food. Will definitely return to try the tacos. This new location is still trying to master their service, but food was delicious and came out quick and hot. Plenty of menu guidance and tons of vegetarian and vegan friendly options. A great place to eat.
The restaurant was beautiful! It was a fantastic atmosphere. I absolutely loved it!

The place was so super good! The service was amazing, and super fast. The Garlic Spicy edename was delicious along with the gyoza. Then the ramen. The ramen was amazing! They give you free noodles at the end! Would highly recommend!

A great dining experience! The staff, setting and food are amazing at Jinya Ramen Bar! My husband and I have never been to a ramen bar until now.  The meals are expertly prepared and DELICIOUS!  I have tried the Spicy Shrimp Ramen and the Wonton Ramen! Both were great! What I loved most is that I did not feel heavy after each meal! Everyone should experience this wonderful restaurant!
Food is OUTSTANDING and the service is great, we love the atmosphere as well! We can't wait to go back and try different things on the menu.
its finally open!

An awesome variety of delicious vegan options. Amazing ramen and great service. A great deal of happy hour options too. This place was worth the wait and does not disappoint. Had the vegan ramen and vegan bun.
Beautiful new restaurant in downtown Alpharetta. Expansive menu. Great service.
Oh My Goodness! This was delicious!

Unbelievable! This location is hands down my favorite one. I have literally gone two days straight. (Lol what can I saya, I love ramen)The food is incredible, the drink selection is vast and the atmosphere is perfect. A location like this is just what this area needed. It is a perfect place to have hot Ramen on a cold day. I love Jinya, I love all their locations but this one takes the cake! If you love ramen go here, if you never had ramen....go here, that is a choice you will not regret.

First time here on opening day and the "Midnight cowboy/Goku" ramen was excellent. The rich creamy broth was perfect with a "subbed thin noodles" and the brisket was thick and tender. A meat lovers pietà.  Also enjoyed the pork buns, the takoyaki were crispy and gooey, the karaage was fried perfectly but most surprisingly, the tempura brussel sprouts were so good I'm going to try it for Thanksgiving 🙈  Atmosphere was busy but not too loud so great for a date night and the service was attentive from all staff, including the chef. The mural by the bar is pretty sweet and of course, nothing cuts a rich broth better than  Sapporo beer. What a great addition to the Alpharetta area!

I had the Red Ramen heat level number 3. The ramen was excellent. Grace took great care of us at the bar. We spoke briefly with the Kitchen Manager as well as Lee the owner. The service was top notch. This will be a hot spot for quite sometime. I can't wait to go back! Enjoy!

Will and his team have another home run with this new location in Downtown Alpharetta. I had the Spicey Chicken bowl and it was to die for! Beautiful, clean, amazing waitstaff! Can’t wait to bring my wife/kids!
Finally a location close enough for lunch breaks. The food was great. The service was awesome. Thanks Lee for bringing Jinya to Alpharetta !
I want to be there for grand opening! Hopefully I can get the golden bowl! 😁
Been to Jinya in Vegas, Houston & both ATL area locations. This is consistently the best ramen. There may be a wait but it's worth it. Just wish there was one closer to Suwanee.
